The paper focuses on using deep neural models for scene text detection and recognition in the context of managing book inventories in a library. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep neural models such as CNNs and RNNs indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the deep learning (cs.DL), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
